CommonFields.Title: Improving mechanical and thermal properties of TiO2-epoxy nanocomposite
Author: Kumar, Kaushal
Ghosh, P.K.
Kumar, Arun
CommonFields.Location: Department of Metallurgical & Materials Engineering, Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee, Roorkee, 247667, India

MatrixComponent.ManufacturerOrSourceName: Fine Finish Organics Pvt. Limited, India

Mixing.Description: epoxy resin and TiO2 mixture was diluted using MEK by the addition of 2 parts of MEK to 1 part of mixture by volume
external cooling was employed by submerging the mixing beaker in an iced water bath

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: DMA analysis were carried out under DMA 8000 (Perkin-Elmer) using single cantilever bending mode at a frequency of 1 Hz with temperature scan. The experimental parameters include a heating rate of 2 C/min and operating temperature range from 40 to 250  C.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The experiment was car- ried out at a heating rate of 10 C/min within the operating tem- perature range from room temperature to 700 C under nitrogen purging with a flow rate of 200 ml/min.
